      "narrative": "TrustDB's concurrency model mirrors SQLite's: single-writer with lock-free readers via CoW snapshots. This is adequate for embedded use but limits write throughput under concurrent load. Notable: TrustDB provides Serializable isolation (stronger than Neo4j's Read Committed), while RocksDB offers concurrent writers but weaker snapshot isolation. The single-writer constraint is a known gap \u2014 multi-writer is on the roadmap.",
